From: Kyle Petryszak <kyle@petryszak.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 00:00:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] phy: rockchip-naneng-combphy: Add PCIe PHY tuning for RK3588

Add PCIe-specific PHY tuning for the RK3588 combo PHY:
- SSC downward spread spectrum configuration
- PCIe receiver detection errata workaround (force_det_out)

These settings are required for reliable PCIe operation with
NBASE-T controllers (RTL8125) on RK3582/RK3588 platforms.

Signed-off-by: Kyle Petryszak <kyle@petryszak.com>
---
 drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c b/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c
index 5b0b3fc8571d..8e0eb52a1edc 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c
@@ -1240,6 +1240,13 @@ static int rk3588_combphy_cfg(struct rockchip_combphy_priv *priv)
 
 	switch (priv->type) {
 	case PHY_TYPE_PCIE:
+		/* Set SSC downward spread spectrum */
+		val = RK3568_PHYREG32_SSC_DOWNWARD << RK3568_PHYREG32_SSC_DIR_SHIFT;
+		rockchip_combphy_updatel(priv, RK3568_PHYREG32_SSC_MASK, val,
+					 RK3568_PHYREG32);
+		/* Enable the counting clock of the rterm detect */
+		rockchip_combphy_updatel(priv, GENMASK(14, 14), BIT(14), 0x86);
+
 		rockchip_combphy_param_write(priv->phy_grf, &cfg->con0_for_pcie, true);
 		rockchip_combphy_param_write(priv->phy_grf, &cfg->con1_for_pcie, true);
 		rockchip_combphy_param_write(priv->phy_grf, &cfg->con2_for_pcie, true);
@@ -1360,6 +1367,9 @@ static int rk3588_combphy_cfg(struct rockchip_combphy_priv *priv)
 		}
 	}
 
+	/* PCIe receiver detection errata workaround */
+	if (priv->type == PHY_TYPE_PCIE)
+		rockchip_combphy_updatel(priv, GENMASK(5, 5), BIT(5), 0x19 << 2);
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
